::Q1::Which Playwright fixture provides a built‑in HTTP client? {=request ~page.request ~newContext}
::Q2::What does response.ok() return true for? {=Status 200–299 ~Only 200 ~Only 2xx and 3xx}
::Q3::Which method is used to create a new isolated API context? {=request.newContext() ~page.request.new() ~browser.newAPIContext()}
::Q4::Which HTTP method is used for partial updates? {=PATCH ~PUT ~UPDATE}
::Q5::Which Playwright method retrieves all response headers as a dictionary? {=response.headers() ~response.headerValues() ~response.headersArray()}
::Q6::Which option is recommended for adding query parameters? {=params object ~string concatenation ~manual URL encoding}
::Q7::What type of auth is used when using page.request after UI login? {=Cookie-based session ~Bearer token ~API key}
::Q8::Which header is typically required for Bearer authentication? {=Authorization ~Auth-Key ~Bearer-Token}
::Q9::Which response format requires using response.body()? {=Binary data ~JSON ~Text}
::Q10::What is the recommended way to seed test data for UI tests? {=API setup ~UI form filling ~Mocking data}
::Q11::Which method obtains multiple values of a repeated header? {=response.headerValues() ~response.headers() ~response.headersArray()}
::Q12::Which status code indicates successful creation of a resource? {=201 ~200 ~204}
::Q13::Which method uploads files via API in Playwright? {=multipart ~fileUpload ~formData}
::Q14::What does request.fetch() allow you to do? {=Use non‑standard HTTP methods ~Send GraphQL queries ~Bypass request context}
::Q15::Which authentication pattern uses Base64 encoded credentials? {=Basic Auth ~Bearer Token ~OAuth2}
::Q16::Which Playwright object shares cookies with the browser session? {=page.request ~request fixture ~newContext}
::Q17::Which matcher asserts that response status is 200–299 and body is not empty? {=toBeOK() ~toBeTruthy() ~toHaveStatus()}
::Q18::Which error range typically triggers retries in flaky external API calls? {=5xx ~4xx ~3xx}
::Q19::What is recommended before reading response.json() in production code? {=Check response.ok() ~Check headers ~Check statusText}
::Q20::Which method is used for polling async server operations? {=Custom pollUntil() ~waitForResponse() ~retryUntilReady()}